articles.author: Jarrett Renshaw, Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Mohammad Salem
articles.description: U.S. President Joe Biden for the first time publicly vowed to withhold weapons from Israel if its forces make a major invasion of Rafah in southern Gaza while negotiations in Cairo on a ceasefire plan for the enclave were due to continue on Thursday.
articles.title: US warns Israel that Rafah invasion will jeopardise weapons supply as assault continues

articles.author: Jack Queen, Luc Cohen, Andy Sullivan
articles.description: Porn star Stormy Daniels will face tough questioning from Donald Trump's lawyers on Thursday as they try to dismantle the credibility of a woman whose story of a 2006 sexual encounter ultimately led to the first criminal trial of a former U.S. president.
articles.title: Stormy Daniels to face tough questions from Trump lawyers at trial

articles.author: Guy Faulconbridge, Vladimir Soldatkin
articles.description: Russian President Vladimir Putin accused the West on Thursday of risking a global conflict and said no one would be allowed to threaten the world's biggest nuclear power as Russia marked the Soviet Union's victory over Nazi Germany in World War Two.
articles.title: Putin warns of global clash as Russia marks victory in World War Two

articles.author: Olena Harmash
articles.description: Within days of Russian forces invading Ukraine in early 2022, architect Oleh Drozdov made up his mind: he would move his home and business from the besieged eastern city of Kharkiv more than 1,000 km to the west, far from the fighting.
articles.title: War upends Ukraine's economy in a shift that may be permanent

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Iran will have to change its nuclear doctrine if its existence is threatened by Israel, an adviser to Iran's Supreme Leader, Kamal Kharrazi said, raising concerns about an Iranian nuclear weapon.
articles.title: Iran to change nuclear doctrine if existence threatened, adviser to Supreme Leader says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Myanmar's military chief discussed plans to hold an election in the country with former Cambodian leader Hun Sen in talks this week, a senior official said, even as the ruling junta faces unprecedented pressure from an expanding armed resistance.
articles.title: Myanmar junta reiterates election plan after ex-Cambodia PM seeks Suu Kyi access

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Britain's opposition Labour Party has increased its poll lead over Prime Minister Rishi Sunak's Conservatives to stand 30 points ahead, according to a YouGov poll for the Times newspaper.
articles.title: UK's Labour holds 30-point poll lead over Sunak's Conservatives

articles.author: Francesco Guarascio
articles.description: Vietnam's foreign affairs ministry has annoyed the European Union by postponing a meeting next week with the EU's top official on Russian sanctions, ahead of a possible visit to Hanoi by Russia's President Vladimir Putin.
articles.title: Vietnam irks EU by delaying meeting ahead of possible Putin visit

articles.author: Josh Smith
articles.description: South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol said on Thursday his government's efforts to improve people's lives had fallen short, as he held a rare news conference to mark his first two years in office.
articles.title: South Korea's Yoon says efforts to improve people's lives had fallen short

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Here are some milestones in Israel's ties with the United States, now strained by Israeli government plans for a major assault on Rafah in southern Gaza and a warning by President Joe Biden that U.S. weapons sales will be withheld if it goes ahead:
articles.title: Biden’s move on weapons supplies is latest test of US-Israel relations
